1
00:00:39,960 --> 00:00:42,119
You're really abusing someone else's power, Xie Fan!

2
00:00:42,359 --> 00:00:44,679
Giant Wood Group only has one second-in-command

3
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:46,200
and that's Zhu Yihai.

4
00:00:46,439 --> 00:00:49,399
Our Dahai is now the number two at Giant Wood Group.

5
00:00:49,960 --> 00:00:51,439
Twelve million.

6
00:00:59,240 --> 00:01:01,600
It's in black and white that you owe her money.

7
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:04,359
Zhu Yihai...

8
00:01:04,359 --> 00:01:06,120
How can you be so shameless?

9
00:01:06,120 --> 00:01:07,879
How could you borrow money from your ex-girlfriend?

10
00:01:07,879 --> 00:01:08,799
You!

11
00:01:08,799 --> 00:01:09,359
Pfft!

12
00:01:10,519 --> 00:01:11,680
And then there was Li Erhu yesterday.

13
00:01:11,920 --> 00:01:12,560
If it'd been you,

14
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:13,680
you'd be locked up again, wouldn't you?

15
00:01:13,920 --> 00:01:15,840
I can't count on you for anything.

16
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:17,719
What can I possibly expect from you?

17
00:01:20,439 --> 00:01:21,359
Who is it?

18
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:24,799
Brother Hai.

19
00:01:26,040 --> 00:01:27,239
Who were you talking to?

20
00:01:28,840 --> 00:01:29,439
It's nothing.

21
00:01:29,799 --> 00:01:30,400
What's up?

22
00:01:33,280 --> 00:01:34,000
Look,

23
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:35,239
what are you thinking?

24
00:01:35,840 --> 00:01:36,879
You gonna pay her back or not?

25
00:01:37,319 --> 00:01:38,400
What do you think?

26
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:38,879
If you ask me,

27
00:01:38,879 --> 00:01:40,879
why let her hold that IOU every day?

28
00:01:40,879 --> 00:01:42,159
Pay it off sooner, cut ties sooner.

29
00:01:42,159 --> 00:01:43,040
Isn't that better?

30
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:45,280
That's what I was thinking too.

31
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:47,920
Dealing with that firecracker every day,

32
00:01:48,079 --> 00:01:49,079
it's exhausting too.

33
00:01:49,079 --> 00:01:51,439
But still, it's almost 70,000 yuan.

34
00:01:52,719 --> 00:01:54,560
We've got Long Xiao backing us now.

35
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:56,079
A few tens of thousands is nothing.

36
00:02:04,959 --> 00:02:05,680
I gotta say,

37
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:07,040
your wife really is

38
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:08,000
quite a character.

39
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:09,360
A real character.

40
00:02:09,879 --> 00:02:12,199
I wonder what I ever saw in her.

41
00:02:13,439 --> 00:02:15,840
So, brother, what brings you to me?

42
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:22,319
Really bad timing.

43
00:02:23,199 --> 00:02:24,199
All the company's cash

44
00:02:24,719 --> 00:02:26,080
is tied up in projects right now.

45
00:02:26,560 --> 00:02:28,400
I barely have any cash on me.

46
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:30,479
It's fine, Brother Long.

47
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:32,719
Forget it if it's inconvenient.

48
00:02:32,719 --> 00:02:34,520
Besides, I didn't come here to borrow money.

49
00:02:34,759 --> 00:02:35,919
I just wanted to ask you,

50
00:02:35,919 --> 00:02:37,759
about that Aimin Street thing you mentioned.

51
00:02:38,479 --> 00:02:39,240
That thing?

52
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:41,319
I think it'll have to wait.

53
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:43,000
You know what?

54
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:45,520
Director Ge is asking sky-high prices now.

55
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:47,719
I feel like this demolition deal

56
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:49,439
is nowhere in sight.

57
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:51,479
I mean, I came in good faith

58
00:02:51,479 --> 00:02:53,000
to help them clean up this mess,

59
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:54,759
and he gives me that attitude.

60
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:56,199
That guy, really...

61
00:02:56,479 --> 00:02:57,960
How can he be like that?

62
00:02:58,479 --> 00:02:59,319
Exactly.

63
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:00,919
Now both of us brothers

64
00:03:01,439 --> 00:03:03,039
are stuck because of that old man.

65
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:06,000
But I gotta say, brother,

66
00:03:06,599 --> 00:03:07,759
you're so easygoing.

67
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:09,120
He owes you money,

68
00:03:09,120 --> 00:03:10,360
and you're not the least bit worried.

69
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:12,800
He... he owes me money?

70
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:14,199
Every laid-off worker like you

71
00:03:14,199 --> 00:03:15,479
is owed severance pay.

72
00:03:15,759 --> 00:03:16,520
Did he give it to you?

73
00:03:16,759 --> 00:03:17,759
Severance pay?

74
00:03:19,039 --> 00:03:19,960
Right.

75
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:21,680
He hasn't paid us our severance yet.

76
00:03:22,159 --> 00:03:24,360
He said it'd be two months when we got laid off.

77
00:03:24,599 --> 00:03:25,560
It's been two years already.

78
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:27,240
What do you think Director Ge

79
00:03:27,719 --> 00:03:29,159
might actually like?

80
00:03:29,439 --> 00:03:32,159
He carries that big tea mug around every day.

81
00:03:32,159 --> 00:03:33,919
What do you think he likes?

82
00:03:33,919 --> 00:03:34,879
The mug!

83
00:03:38,639 --> 00:03:39,759
Give me our tea leaves.

84
00:03:43,319 --> 00:03:44,159
They're right here.

85
00:03:52,879 --> 00:03:53,680
This'll do.

86
00:04:00,039 --> 00:04:00,840
Director Ge.

87
00:04:01,439 --> 00:04:02,240
Who is it?

88
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:05,199
It's me, Little Zhu from the factory.

89
00:04:06,039 --> 00:04:06,680
Little Zhu?

90
00:04:07,199 --> 00:04:08,280
I don't know you.

91
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:10,680
What's up?

92
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:11,960
What do you want?

93
00:04:13,879 --> 00:04:14,840
I came over here

94
00:04:15,159 --> 00:04:16,600
because I really need to talk to you.

95
00:04:17,439 --> 00:04:19,879
About that severance pay thing.

96
00:04:21,839 --> 00:04:22,839
Severance pay?

97
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:25,399
Easy enough.

98
00:04:25,399 --> 00:04:26,120
Sit, sit, sit.

99
00:04:27,920 --> 00:04:29,360
Severance pay...

100
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:31,279
Easy, easy.

101
00:04:31,279 --> 00:04:32,519
Severance pay...

102
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:35,839
Severance pay...

103
00:04:38,920 --> 00:04:41,360
This hexagram's hard to read.

104
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:47,800
Severance pay...

105
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:48,920
Director.

106
00:04:49,199 --> 00:04:50,000
Take a look.

107
00:04:50,319 --> 00:04:51,600
This should solve it, right?

108
00:04:53,759 --> 00:04:54,680
What's this?

109
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:56,160
Tea leaves.

110
00:04:57,680 --> 00:04:58,240
Tea leaves?

111
00:04:58,560 --> 00:04:59,360
Tea leaves.

112
00:05:02,879 --> 00:05:03,800
Tea leaves!

113
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:05,959
With tea leaves, it's easy.

114
00:05:08,519 --> 00:05:09,720
Severance pay...

115
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:14,879
Look at this hexagram.

116
00:05:15,399 --> 00:05:16,319
It's solved.

117
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:17,639
Just like that, solved.

118
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,600
With tea leaves, it's easy.

119
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:20,439
Solved, great.

120
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:25,399
Ge...

121
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:27,639
Zhendong!

122
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:30,879
Go see the accountant.

123
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:32,079
Okay.

124
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,000
Thank you, Director.

125
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:39,319
Director,

126
00:05:39,879 --> 00:05:40,480
muah!

127
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:51,079
Have a seat.

128
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:53,720
It's, it's fine.

129
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:54,560
I'll just stand, it's okay.

130
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:55,519
Sit down.

131
00:05:55,839 --> 00:05:56,879
No need to be so formal.

132
00:05:57,680 --> 00:05:58,480
What's up?

133
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:01,879
Director Ge sent me over.

134
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:04,160
He told me to come pick up the severance pay.

135
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:14,519
How'd you pull that off?

136
00:06:14,759 --> 00:06:16,279
I gave him a pack of tea leaves.

137
00:06:16,279 --> 00:06:17,639
And then he sent me right over.

138
00:06:17,759 --> 00:06:18,560
Tea leaves.

139
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:25,959
This is for you.

140
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:36,319
Why didn't I ever think of that?

141
00:06:36,759 --> 00:06:38,120
No wonder all these years,

142
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:39,879
I never got named Outstanding Worker.

143
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:41,759
That brain of yours, really.

144
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:44,079
You're really something else.

145
00:06:55,079 --> 00:06:56,079
It's literally just tea.

146
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:57,800
It's actually just tea leaves.

147
00:06:58,240 --> 00:06:59,800
But it's good tea, you know!

148
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:04,959
Hello?

149
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:06,519
Hello, Accountant Liu.

150
00:07:06,879 --> 00:07:07,519
Director Ge.

151
00:07:07,639 --> 00:07:08,759
Is Zhu Yihai there with you?

152
00:07:08,839 --> 00:07:09,480
Yeah, he's here.

153
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:13,800
Stand up first.

154
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:16,680
I, I'm not even sitting.

155
00:07:17,079 --> 00:07:17,879
Hey.

156
00:07:21,199 --> 00:07:22,560
Tell him to get the hell out, now.

157
00:07:22,879 --> 00:07:23,680
Scram.

158
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:30,720
He's pissing me off!

159
00:07:31,399 --> 00:07:32,439
Took my tea leaves,

160
00:07:32,639 --> 00:07:33,639
and then told me to scram!

161
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:35,959
Don't get mad just yet.

162
00:07:35,959 --> 00:07:37,319
Have some peanuts, cool off.

163
00:07:37,319 --> 00:07:38,079
Brother Hai.

164
00:07:38,079 --> 00:07:39,160
Let's call in the crew.

165
00:07:40,240 --> 00:07:41,279
Dali, put that down right now.

166
00:07:41,279 --> 00:07:42,519
What are you trying to do?

167
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:50,519
Wei Wei.

168
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:52,319
I'll give you three minutes.

169
00:07:52,519 --> 00:07:54,160
Get me everything on Director Ge.

170
00:07:56,959 --> 00:07:57,800
Three minutes.

171
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:02,199
I asked around.

172
00:08:02,959 --> 00:08:05,319
Director Ge fears nothing on earth,

173
00:08:05,879 --> 00:08:07,720
but he's super damn superstitious.

174
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,279
Did you hear about it?

175
00:08:10,279 --> 00:08:12,639
Lao Luo's whole family of four, you know...

176
00:08:12,639 --> 00:08:13,759
What about them?

177
00:08:13,759 --> 00:08:15,839
Don't even ask, it's awful.

178
00:08:16,079 --> 00:08:17,680
They never got their severance pay.

179
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:19,399
Driven to their deaths!

180
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:21,120
That actually happened?

181
00:08:59,399 --> 00:08:59,960
Hey.

182
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:02,519
I'm so cold.

183
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:08,799
I'm so cold.

184
00:09:09,879 --> 00:09:15,600
A family of four froze to death in white clothes.

185
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:19,080
Who's there?

186
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:20,639
Quit playing tricks!

187
00:09:21,559 --> 00:09:22,480
What's wrong with you?

188
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:42,879
Director Ge!

189
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:46,879
What about my severance pay?

190
00:09:46,879 --> 00:09:48,559
Director Ge!

191
00:09:48,559 --> 00:09:52,120
You've ruined me!

192
00:09:57,799 --> 00:09:59,639
You've ruined me!

193
00:09:59,639 --> 00:10:01,559
You've ruined me!

194
00:10:01,559 --> 00:10:03,240
Director Ge!

195
00:10:05,879 --> 00:10:07,559
Director Ge!

196
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:24,159
Lao Luo.

197
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:27,600
Every debt has its debtor.

198
00:10:30,039 --> 00:10:31,039
I had no idea

199
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:33,720
your family was so broke you couldn't even eat.

200
00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:37,799
Who?

201
00:10:56,320 --> 00:10:57,679
Ge Zhendong!

202
00:10:59,759 --> 00:11:01,399
You dropped something.

203
00:11:08,559 --> 00:11:09,440
Ge Zhendong!

204
00:11:14,960 --> 00:11:16,399
Ge Zhendong!

205
00:11:18,039 --> 00:11:19,919
I'm sorry, my lady, I was wrong!

206
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:23,519
Uncle Ge, come play with us!

207
00:11:23,519 --> 00:11:26,039
Lao Luo, just tell me if you're broke.

208
00:11:26,039 --> 00:11:27,240
Don't scare me like that!

209
00:11:27,240 --> 00:11:28,279
Uncle Ge!

210
00:11:28,279 --> 00:11:29,960
You wouldn't pay us while we were alive.

211
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:31,519
Will you burn it for us now?

212
00:11:31,519 --> 00:11:33,519
I'll pay, I'll pay right now!

213
00:11:33,519 --> 00:11:35,639
I'll give you everything.

214
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:38,240
Give us our severance pay!

215
00:11:39,159 --> 00:11:40,840
Uncle Ge!

216
00:11:41,240 --> 00:11:41,960
Pay up!

217
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:42,960
I already paid!

218
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:44,080
Pay up!

219
00:11:44,639 --> 00:11:45,759
I want my money!

220
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:49,600
What are you guys doing here?

221
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:50,919
Playing duck duck goose at midnight?

222
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:57,200
Carry on, then.

223
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:04,240
Zhu Yihai!

224
00:12:04,240 --> 00:12:05,000
We're screwed!

225
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:05,799
Run!

226
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:06,960
Stop right there!

227
00:12:10,519 --> 00:12:11,320
Who's there?

228
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:15,759
Hui Lian?

229
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:17,200
Hui Lian.

230
00:12:19,559 --> 00:12:20,919
You little brats.

231
00:12:21,279 --> 00:12:22,360
Damn, they run fast.

232
00:12:22,919 --> 00:12:24,240
Don't let me catch you.

233
00:12:29,840 --> 00:12:30,919
What are you doing here?

234
00:12:30,919 --> 00:12:31,840
Director Ge.

235
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:32,879
I'm on duty.

236
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:34,120
What are you up to?

237
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:35,919
Something happened to Lao Luo.

238
00:12:35,919 --> 00:12:36,759
Lao Luo?

239
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:38,519
We just had a late-night snack.

240
00:12:38,759 --> 00:12:39,480
He went home.

241
00:12:39,799 --> 00:12:40,480
Really?

242
00:12:41,399 --> 00:12:42,639
What happened to your pants?

243
00:12:42,639 --> 00:12:43,360
They're wet.

244
00:12:56,919 --> 00:12:58,559
What's the next step in the plan?
